  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Endoscopic Healing Rate Over 8 Weeks of Erosive Esophagitis</measure>
    <time_frame>8 Weeks</time_frame>
    <description>Endoscopic healing of erosive esophagitis is defined as those participants who have endoscopically confirmed EE of Grade O as defined by the Los Angeles (LA) Classification Grading System. The definitions of each grade are: Grade O (No mucosal break), Grade A (Mucosal break &lt;5 mm), Grade B (Mucosal break ≥5 mm), Grade C (Mucosal break continuous between two or more folds and &lt;75% of the circumference) and Grade D (Mucosal break ≥75% of the circumference).</description>
  </primary_outcome>
